 in extracting answers for text data in order to support business decision making. Most of the exercises use Excel, today’s most common analysis tool, and R, a popular analytic computer environment. The techniques covered range from the most basic text analytics, such as key word analysis, to more sophisticated techniques, such as topic extraction and text similarity scoring. Companion files with numerous datasets are included for use with case studies and exercises. Features: Organized by tool or technique, with the basic techniques presented first and the more sophisticated techniques presented later Uses Excel and R for datasets in case studies and exercises Features the CRISP-DM data mining standard with early chapters for conducting the preparatory steps in data mining Companion files with numerous datasets and figures from the text. The companion files are available online by emailing the publisher with proof of purchase at info@merclearning.com.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDecision makingxData processingvCase studies. 4aData. 4aHuman Resource Management. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Business Communication / General.2bisacsh  aBusiness Communication.  aComputer Science.  aData Analytics.  aData Visualization.  aExcel.  aR.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024z97831115024960 cEPUBz97816839266410 cprintz978168392666540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978168392665840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781683926658423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781683926658/original  a978-3-11-150249-6  Sciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024b2024  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  a